Package sample

  • Interface Summary 
    Interface Description
    Item
    Dictates that all products must have methods for getting id, as well as getting and setting the product name and manufacturer.
    MultimediaControl
    Dictates that all multimedia player objects shall play and stop songs, as well as skip to the previous and next tracks.
    ScreenSpec
    Dictates that all screens attached to a multimedia player contain methods to get the screen's resolution size, refresh rate, and response time.
  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    AudioPlayer
    An audio player.
    AudioPlayerDriver
    A simple main loop to test the creation of an AudioPlayer object.
    Controller
    As of 10/27/2019, this class does nothing.
    DatabaseManager
    Manages all database activity including connecting to the database and executing SQL statements.
    Main
    This program is a simple JavaFX program with 3 tabs and the ability to connect to a database and execute SQL statements.
    MoviePlayer
    A movie player.
    MoviePlayerDriver
    A simple main loop to test the creation of an MoviePlayer object.
    MultimediaControlDriver
    Demonstrates polymorphism by showing that any class implementing MultimediaControl can be instantiated, and that the methods defined in MultimediaControl can be used regardless of the class that implements it.
    Product
    Contains a generic Product class that is used abstractly as a template for specific products.
    Production
    Represents a manufacturing production record of a product.
    Screen
    Stores information about the screen attached to a Product.
    ScreenDriver
    A simple main loop to test the creation of an Screen object.
    Widget
    Temporary class for testing the Product class functionality.
  • Enum Summary 
    Enum Description
    ItemType
    Specifies the "type" of a product - that is, whether it is audio-based or visual-based, and whether it is mobile or not.
    MonitorType
    Specifies the types of visual display monitors that may be used by a Product.
